node.text:
Diving deep and free, just the water and me 😌

Ginnie Springs is a privately owned park in Gilchrist County about 6.5 miles (10.5 km) northwest of High Springs, Florida, USA. It is located on the south side of the Santa Fe River, to which it is connected. The water is clear and cold and there are accessible caverns with a sand and limestone bottom.

Ginnie Springs has been privately owned by the Wray family since 1971 and began functioning in 1976. In the mid-1990s when scuba diving grew in popularity, Bob Wray opened the springs to the public. The popularity of Ginnie took off and it became a nationally renowned diving spot which is still largely popular today.

📽 @andrewdesloover w/ @bjgriffinmusic
📍Ginnie Springs, Florida

Canada's breathtaking spots via @mthiessen. 🌈 From natural landscapes to clean and modern cities, Canada is as picturesque as it gets when it comes to spectacular scenery. 🇨🇦

Swipe through and marvel at these incredible places! Save this post for reference when you visit Canada. 📝

@Nature Destinations in Canada
1-3. Niagara Falls, Ontario
4. Spirit Island, Alberta
5. Jasper, Alberta
6. Golden fields near Stony Plain, Alberta
7. Emerald Lake, British Columbia
8. Moraine Lake Road, Alberta
9. Lake Louise, Alberta
10. Edmonton, Alberta

Which one is your favorite? 👇

📸 @mthiessen
📍 Canada

node.text:
Switzerland's cliff walk is for thrill-seekers only via @michelphotographych 🇨🇭Would you be brave enough to walk through this high walkway suspended from a rocky mountainside, with peak & valley views, accessed by gondola?

About 300 meters long. It takes just 10-15 minutes to walk it in one direction, photo stops included. If you want to walk it both ways, count about half an hour for your visit.

The First Cliff Walk in Switzerland wraps around the mountains of Grindelwald and is a breathtaking experience for those brave enough to embark on the hike up the Bernese Alps. Most of the area is car free, First included. Grindelwald itself can be reached by car, but for nearly all other places you can travel by train and cable cars only.

Travel Tips: The easiest way to get to First Cliff Walk is by taking a 25-minutes gondola ride from Grindelwald to First. From there, it's just a short walk of 5 minutes to the Cliff Walk. You cannot drive up to First by car or by bus and hiking here from Grindelwald would take you several hours.

📽 @michelphotographych
📍Grindelwald, Switzerland
🎶 Ben Pellow - Roslyn

node.text:
Color overload in Balat, Istanbul 🌈
Which of these photos is your favorite? Have you been to Istanbul before? 🇹🇷 

In lovely Balat, sidewalk cafes and European-Turkish bistros share the streets with old wooden houses and small, stately churches like the Saint Stefan Bulgarian Orthodox Church, made of cast iron, and the 7th-century Church of St. Mary of the Mongols. Along the waterfront, İbb Haliç Şair Nedim Parkı has walking paths and a ferry terminal, with connections down the Golden Horn and across to the city’s Asian side.

From 1-10, which is your favorite photo? Would you like to explore this neighborhood someday? 🇹🇷

📸 @mstfatyfn
📍 Balat, Istanbul, Turkey

Devil’s Pool is a natural pool of water that’s situated atop of Victoria Falls, renown for being among the largest waterfalls in the world. Right on the edge of this massive waterfall, a calm pool of water forms.

This is known as the Devil’s Pool Victoria Falls. And daring visitors can actually swim in this pool straddling the edge of Victoria Falls!

📽 @abenafrica
📍Zambia and Zimbabwe
🎶 Ikson - Apart

node.text:
The Land of Legends in Turkey 😍 Unleash your adventurous spirit at Turkey’s first magical kingdom. Packed to the brim with entertainment to suit any taste, a holiday here ensures a legendary and unforgettable experience for all the family. From the on-site theme park to the Venetian-style canals, the Land of Legends is sure to live up to its name.

📽 @waelalteen
📍Antalya, Turkey
🎶 Hailey Barnes & Calvin Jenkins - Lovely
